parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Direct Ignition Cassette can cause the engine to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can result in a dangerous situation, especially if the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: Engine stalling or failure to start
loss of power steering and brakes
check engine light illumination
and sudden shutdown of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the sudden deployment of the airbag without an impact or crash, which can cause injuries or accidents.
symptoms: Sudden deployment of the airbag without an impact or crash
airbag indicator illumination
and wiring issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower switch and wiring can cause a fire hazard, especially if the blower motor continues to run without shutting off.
symptoms: Erratic blower switch behavior
failure of the blower to turn off
and melted wires and connectors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Ignition Discharge Module can cause the engine to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can result in a dangerous situation, especially if the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: Engine stalling or failure to start
loss of power steering and brakes
and sudden shutdown of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dash information display can cause a safety issue, especially if the display is illegible or fails to report important information, such as temperature or mechanical problems.
symptoms: Burned-out or disappeared pixels on the display
and illegible or incomplete information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, including facial lacerations, concussions, and inner ear damage, and can lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without warning or impact
airbag deploys while the vehicle is parked or in motion
airbag deploys without any prior warning lights or service codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbag to Deploy in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in a crash
airbag light illuminates on the dashboard
airbag system malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to pull to one side while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to the left or right while driving
the vehicle drifts from left to right when driving at high speeds
the steering jerks or becomes unstable
there is excessive play in the wheel
the vehicle moves to the right or left side when driving over grooves in the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cradle bolt can cause the vehicle's suspension to become unstable, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The cradle bolt head is found under the vehicle
the cradle bolt appears to be fractured
the vehicle's suspension is unstable.
